The paper discusses techniques for reducing channel state information (CSI) acquisition overhead in multiuser multiple-input-multiple-output (MU-MIMO) systems, which are commonly used in wireless communications. This topic falls under the intersection of several computer science sub-disciplines, including information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), systems and control (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and computer communications (cs.COM). However, given the focus on wireless communications and signal processing, cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely sub-categories.
